==Post-structuralism?==
I've done some "light" reading on the subject and I have never seen post-structuralism referred to as existing within postmodernism from any reputable source, and the only source used to reference this section is a third party wiki. I'm going to remove it for now, and also look a little closer at structuralism when I have the time, as this section also seems a bit "iffy". [[Special:Contributions/47.54.207.107|47.54.207.107]] ([[User talk:47.54.207.107|talk]]) 00:37, 3 November 2015 (UTC)

== Nihilism ==

Postmodernism is similar to [[nihilism]] because "incredulity towards meta-narratives" is very similar to a "disbelief in everything"; maybe this similarity should be mentioned without citations because that fact is more of common knowledge. Postmodernism would also rejects this similarity in a neither a negating nor affirming manner though. And the previous sentence and what ever other clause, etc. —User '''[[User:User000name|0]][[User_talk:User000name|0]][[Special:Contributions/User000name|0]]''' name 19:25, 21 April 2016 (UTC)
